Package org.jpedal.examples.viewer.commands

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AccelerationOff
    Toggles Acceleration Off in the Viewer
    AccelerationOn
    Toggles Acceleration On in the Viewer
    Add
    This class allows you to add a page to your PDF document, using itext function .add().
    AddHeaderFooter
    This class allows you to add a header and a footer (usually the page number) to the top and bottom of each page in the opened document.
    AlwaysShowMouse  
    AutoScroll
    togglesAutoScrolling on or off for Viewer
    BitMap
    Save the PDF document as a BitMap
    Bookmark
    Bookmark the current page in the Viewer
    Buy
    Code to handle Buy button we display in demo versions of Viewer
    Cascade
    Cascades all the window frames
    ChangeLineArt  
    Continuous  
    ContinuousFacing  
    Copy
    Copies the text a user has selected/highlighted.
    CurrentPage  
    Delete
    Deleted selected pages from the Document, uses itext functions delete() It then re-open the document excluding the deleted pages.
    DeletePropertiesOnExit  
    DeSelectAll
    Deselects the text/image a user has highlighted in the Viewer
    DocInfo
    Shows a Message Dialogue displaying the Documents Information
    Exit
    Clean up and exit programo
    ExtractSelectionAsImage
    This class is a Swing specific class to hold the Swing code for Extracting the drawn CursorBox as an Image.
    ExtractText
    Class to Handle the popup dialogs created when user right clicks highlighted text and chooses text extraction.
    Facing  
    Find
    Find designated text and highlight it in the Viewer
    FullScreen  
    Handouts  
    Help
    Code to handle Help button we display in demo versions of Viewer
    Highlight
    This class allows you to Highlight a selected text/image using Rectangles by getting the text lines.
    Images
    Extract/Save Images
    Info
    Code to handle Info button we display in demo versions of Viewer
    MouseModeCommand
    Sets the selection mouse to MouseMode
    NavigateDocuments
    This class Opens up a previously opened document, you can open either a previous document or the next document in the Viewer.
    NextResults
    Shows the next lot of search results in the Viewer
    Nup  
    OpenFile
    This class Opens up a new file on page one whilst still using the users chosen settings, it first handles unsaved forms and resets the viewable area, it decodes the PDF and finally opens the new document.
    PageCount
    Count the number of pages the current document in the Viewer has
    PageFlow  
    PageGrouping
    Group Pages in Viewer
    PageNavigator
    This class controls the different methods that allow you to navigate a document by page, its critical method is navigatePages()
    PanMode
    Enables Pan Mode in the Viewer which enables the user to Pan the Document
    Pdf  
    Preferences
    Shows the Preferences Dialog Box
    PreviousResult  
    Print
    Print the current document
    Quality
    Increases the quality by using Hi-Res images in the Viewer
    ReplaceTextColor
    Flags when current text color should be changed
    Reset  
    Rotate
    This class Rotates the selected documents pages clockwise by 90*, it uses itexts rotate method.
    Rotation
    Rotates the current document in the Viewer This class is Generic and does not need a specific Swing/JavaFX implementation.
    RSSyndication
    Code to handle RSS button we display in demo versions of Viewer
    SaveFile
    Saves the current document file
    SaveForm
    Saves the form and sends data to database server
    Scaling  
    Scroll
    Allows the user to scroll through the PDF document at a scroll interval scroll interval is default of 10 unless changed.
    Security
    This class allows you to encrypt the current page of the document which adds a level of security.
    SelectAll
    Selects and highlights everything in the document
    SeperateCover  
    SetCommand  
    SetCrop
    This class provides a method that will set the crop rectangle for the pages of your PDF document.
    SetDisplayBackground  
    SetPageColor
    Sets the page colour of the current loaded document in the Viewer
    SetReplacementThreshold  
    SetTextColor
    Sets the documents text color in the Viewer
    SetUndrawnPageColor
    Sets the Color of pages that havn't been drawn yet
    ShowFormNames
    Shows the names of all the forms of the current document
    Sign  
    Single  
    StampImage
    This class allows you to place selected images repeatedly on the pages of your document It will print the current page count, the page data and a stampImage sent into itext function stampImage()
    StampText
    This class allows you to place selected text repeatedly on the pages of your document It will print the current page umber, the page data and a string of text sent into itext function stampText()
    Text
    Saves the text from a page rage / current selection, cannot export from a URL.
    TextSelect
    Enable Text Selection in Viewer
    Tile
    Tiles all the window frames
    Tip
    Code to handle the Tip of the day feature we display in theViewer
    Toggle  
    UpdateGUILayout
    Updates the layout of the page
    Viewable
    a view of a defined page, Rectangle on page, and scalingtype
    ViewStack
    the view stack type object that allows us to store views as they change and then go back through them as needed.
    VisitWebsite
    This class is generic for both Swing and JavaFX.
